article.description: — Noel Coleman scored 21 points and Hawaii held off Texas State 72-65 in the North Shore Classic on Saturday night.
article.headline: Coleman leads Hawaii to 72-65 victory over Texas State
article.linkText: Coleman leads Hawaii to 72-65 victory over Texas State
article.story: LAIE, Hawaii -- — Noel Coleman scored 21 points and Hawaii held off Texas State 72-65 in the North Shore Classic on Saturday night. Coleman sank 6 of 11 shots with two 3-pointers and made 7 of 9 foul shots for the Rainbow Warriors (5-1). Bernardo Da Silva pitched in with 14 points and seven rebounds. Harry Rouhliadeff had 11 points off the bench and Jovon McClanahan scored 10. Mason Harrell topped the Bobcats (4-3) with 23 points. Brandon Davis finished with 12 points and seven rebounds. ----
